{"title":"4.1 Create frame and select sample","markdown":{"headingText":"4.1 Create frame and select sample","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n## Process\n\nThis sub-process creates or updates the frame (e.g. statistical business, household) and selects the sample for this iteration of the collection, as specified in sub-process 2.4 (Design frame and sample).\nIt also includes the coordination of samples between instances of the same statistical process (e.g. to manage overlap or rotation), and between different processes using a common frame or register (e.g. to manage overlap or to spread response burden).\nQuality assurance and approval of the frame and the selected sample are also undertaken in this sub-process, though maintenance of underlying registers, from which frames for several statistical business processes are drawn, is treated as a separate statistical process.\nThe sampling aspect of this sub-process is not usually relevant for processes based entirely on the use of pre-existing sources (e.g. administrative registers, web sites) as such processes generally create frames from the availablae data and then follow a census approach.\nVariables from administrative and other non-statistical sources of data can be used as auxiliary variables in the construction of sampling frame.\n\n## Input\n\n- A datasource for creating the frame\n- [Output from sub-Process 2.4](../Process2/2.4.md)\n- maps (Geo)\n- [Outputs from sub-process 2.2](../Process2/2.2.md)\n\n## Output\n\n- Sampling units\n- Selected samples\n- Sampling frame\n\n## Documentation and Tools\n\n- Household listing manual\n- Strategy for developing and maintaining SBR\n- Listing forms\n- R-code (scripts)\n\n## Latest update\n\n19th March 2024\n\n## Verified\n\n_date_\n\n<button onclick=\"history.back()\">Go Back</button>\n\n[Go to Home page](../index.md)\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width